J.P. Morgan's Shao Zili to Become Vice Chairman of Asian-Pacific Region
Mr. Shao's Move Marks Second Major Change in Bank's China Leadership in Past Month

 






By

Dinny McMahon


Dinny McMahon
The Wall Street Journal
BiographyDinny McMahon
@DinnyMcMahon
dinny.mcmahon@wsj.com




  April 18, 2014 3:43 a.m. ET





BEIJING—The chairman and chief executive in China for J.P. Morgan Chase & Co., Shao Zili, is set to leave those roles and become its vice chairman for the Asian-Pacific region. This marks second major change in the bank's China leadership in the past month. According to a memo reviewed by The Wall Street Journal and confirmed by a spokeswoman for the bank, Mr. Shao's new role will involve regional projects and advising the bank's...
  


