News & Insights


News


Mr. Zili Shao will join KWM China












King & Wood Mallesons (KWM) will soon welcome a high profile business leader, Mr. Zili Shao, to join the firm’s China practice. 
Mr. Zili Shao is a highly accomplished lawyer and investment banker with extensive professional experience and is well-known in the Asian commercial world for his achievements. Mr. Shao has previously held positions as Chairman and CEO of J.P. Morgan China and Vice Chairman of J.P. Morgan Asia Pacific. Prior to that, he acted as managing partner of Linklaters for Greater China and subsequently was appointed managing partner of the Asia region. Mr. Shao will join the firm as Co-Chairman of KWM China’s Management Committee. 
Wang Ling, Managing Partner of KWM China, said, “Zili is a long term friend of the firm, and has always followed our development and growth. We look forward to Zili joining the firm and believe he will play a key role in the globalization of the firm.”
“We are delighted to have someone of Zili’s calibre join our firm in China. His breadth of experience across the legal and corporate sector and deep knowledge of the region provides him with theability to help lead KWM through its' next stage of development in China, and to help to integrate the China practice into the global KWM firm,” said Stuart Fuller, Global Managing Partner. 









